The decade of the Second China ShockBrace yourselves. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-decade-of-the-second-china-shock https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-decade-of-the-second-china-shockNoah Smith Sat, 23 Mar 2024 03:31:57 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg" width="680" height="494" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:494,&quot;width&quot;:680,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:62091,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe7ee2fb1-3963-4827-9684-fc058236f0e9_680x494.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.cfr.org/blog/chinas-record-manufacturing-surplus">CFR</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> 2000年代是第一次中国冲击的十年。据我所知，“中国冲击”一词是由经济学家大卫·奥托、大卫·多恩和戈登·汉森在<a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w21906">2016年的一篇著名论文</a>中创造的。我毫不夸张地说，如果你只知道过去十年的一篇经济论文，那就应该是这篇。这就像一颗流星坠入了经济界。在 Autor 等人之前。 （2016）“自由贸易是好事”是经济学界<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/26/upshot/economists-actually-agree-on-this-point-the-wisdom-of-free-trade.html">最不可动摇的共识</a>；论文发表后，这种共识就被打破了。</p><p>什么奥托等人。事实表明，2000 年代，与中国的贸易摧毁了大批美国劳动力。在之前的贸易扩张中，一些制造业工人因与德国、日本或印度尼西亚进口产品的竞争而被取代，但通常他们只是在制造业的其他地方找到了工作。 2000年代的中国完全不同。竞争如此迅速、突然、如此激烈，并且遍及各个可以想象的行业，以至于美国工厂的工人无处可去。许多人永久性地转入服务行业工作，这些工作的工资比以前低得多（例如：收银员、油炸厨师等）。有些人进入了福利名单。</p><p>从理论上讲，这不应该引起经济领域的如此大的地震。经济学家一直认为，贸易会导致“赢家和输家”（礼貌的委婉说法是“将你的工作转移到中国的股东成为百万富翁，而你则成为汉堡包爱好者”）。每个模型都同意这一点<a class="footnote-anchor" data-component-name="FootnoteAnchorToDOM" id="footnote-anchor-1" href="#footnote-1" target="_self">1</a> 。但直到 2000 年代的中国冲击之前，他们并没有真正<em>相信</em>损失会如此惨重。同年特朗普当选——<a href="https://www.ddorn.net/papers/ADHM-PoliticalPolarization.pdf">许多</a><a href="https://www.nber.org/papers/w21899">论文</a>将其与贸易相关的失业联系在一起——似乎已经敲定了这一点。自由贸易并不总是值得庆祝的事情。</p><p>但至少经济学家可以告诉自己，中国冲击已经<em>结束</em>。奥托等人。 （2016）和其他研究人员随后的论文发现，中国的进口竞争在 2010 年左右，甚至<a href="https://d101vc9winf8ln.cloudfront.net/documents/30626/original/BHKL_3-20-19_v2.pdf?1554902707">稍早一些</a>就停止了加剧。这与我们在美国制造业总就业图表中所看到的情况非常吻合（尽管显然大衰退也是其中的一部分）： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:59532,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5770c8d9-20fc-4025-ba3d-226f22027ddd_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>因此，人们普遍认为，这是一次性的——我们富裕国家可以从 2010 年代的碉堡中，饱受摧残、睡眼惺忪地走出来，带着我们剩下的制造业跌跌撞撞地前进，而不必担心会再次发生。毕竟，如果你看看日本、德国或其他过去竞争对手的历史贸易竞争，你会发现，随着时间的推移，它似乎达到了顶峰，然后趋于平稳或下降。</p><p>但中国在很多方面都与其他竞争对手不同。从上图（取自 Brad Setser 和 Michael Weilandt<a href="https://www.cfr.org/blog/chinas-record-manufacturing-surplus">最近发表的博客文章）</a>中可以看出，中国的制造业盈余（相对于其贸易伙伴的 GDP 衡量）在 2010 年之后并没有停止攀升。多年来，它再次飙升，达到了日本或德国从未梦想过的高度。与此同时，头条新闻<a href="https://www.wsj.com/world/china/the-world-is-in-for-another-china-shock-3d98b533">开始敲响第二次中国冲击的警报</a>。</p><p>这次新的贸易冲击将成为 2020 年代最重要的经济故事之一。因此，我们需要了解它——它是什么、为什么会发生、它与 2000 年代的第一次中国冲击有何不同，以及我们可能想对此做些什么。</p><h4>第二次中国冲击是什么以及为什么会发生</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-decade-of-the-second-china-shock">阅读更多</a></p>; 
