&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:683,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:712,&quot;bytes&quot;:48520,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb46bf88f-1849-42ee-ae2a-28bf45a6af4a_1024x683.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb46bf88f-1849-42ee-ae2a-28bf45a6af4a_1024x683.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb46bf88f-1849-42ee-ae2a-28bf45a6af4a_1024x683.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb46bf88f-1849-42ee-ae2a-28bf45a6af4a_1024x683.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/147601527@N04">Solen Feyissa</a>的“ <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/147601527@N04/50179261657">Tiktok</a> ”， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC BY-SA 2.0</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> In the world of crypto, to get “rug-pulled”, or “rugged”, means to be <a href="https://www.coindesk.com/learn/what-is-a-rug-pull-how-to-protect-yourself-from-getting-rugged/">scammed out of your investment</a> .通常情况下，一些匿名支持者会炒作某种加密货币或 NFT 等，然后带着投资者的现金消失。</p><p>加密货币是有风险的，但民粹主义政治世界也是如此。 Many conservatives who care deeply about national security chose to invest their hopes and their political support in Donald Trump, on the theory that he&#39;s tough on China. During his first term, this seemed to clearly be the case. Trump ditched the long-standing policy of engagement with China, slapped major tariffs on Chinese goods, implemented export controls on Huawei, initiated a hunt for Chinese spies in academia, tried (unsuccessfully) to force ByteDance to sell TikTok to an American company, and blamed Covid squarely on China.拜登继续这种鹰派方法，但特朗普是原始的。因此，对于保守派，假设如果特朗普当选，他将对CCP承受压力。</p><p> Trump&#39;s <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2024/02/10/politics/trump-foreign-aid-loan-senate-package/index.html">turn against aid to Ukraine</a> only put a slight dent in that hope. Conservatives like Elbridge Colby, who have <a href="https://time.com/6696552/u-s-hawks-china-threat-essay/">been arguing</a> in favor of a refocusing away from Europe and the Middle East and toward Asia, were able to see the turn against Ukraine aid as an opportunity rather than as an ominous warning. If Trump forced the Europeans to take the lead in holding the line against Russia, while pivoting US attention and power toward China, all would be well. Buoyed by this hope, and watching traditional conservatives like Ron DeSantis and Nikki Haley fall before the MAGA juggernaut, natsec conservatives have been reconciling themselves to the idea of Trump 2024.</p><p> But this past week, that hope was pretty conclusively dashed.</p><p>国会和拜登政府都在零星的努力迫使中国公司派遣Tiktok将Tiktok出售给一家非中国公司，但这些努力并没有发生。然后，上周突然，众议院<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/03/07/house-committee-unanimously-supports-forcing-tiktok-divestiture.html">提出了一项法案</a>，以迫使提克托克出售，理由是它是“外国对手控制的申请”。 (You can <a href="https://d1dth6e84htgma.cloudfront.net/TIKTOK_xml_655b9d7933.pdf">read the text of the bill here</a> , if you&#39;re interested.)</p><p> TikTok launched <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-68517607">a desperate all-out campaign</a> to keep the bill from getting out of committee. The app sent a push notification to its users, urging them to call their representatives and stop the bill. The campaign failed, and the bill passed the committee 50-0, with leaders of both parties voicing thunderous support. <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2024/03/08/tiktok-ban-biden-sign-congress-trump/">拜登说</a>，如果国会通过了，他将签署。</p><p> And then, suddenly, the Chinese company found a savior. That savior&#39;s name was Donald Trump.在一次令人惊叹的逆转中，特朗普<a href="https://qz.com/donald-trump-tiktok-ban-bytedance-joe-biden-sotu-1851319392">出来了，</a>反对Tiktok禁令：</p><blockquote><p> Donald Trump appeared to come out in defense of <a href="https://qz.com/bill-that-could-make-tiktok-unavailable-in-the-us-advan-1851317789">TikTok, the social media platform facing a potential ban by Congress</a> , in a post late Thursday on his social media platform Truth Social — the same platform that experienced a <a href="https://gizmodo.com/truth-social-down-outage-trump-biden-state-of-the-union-1851318732">widespread outage</a> as the former president attempted to live -Tweet总统乔·拜登（Joe Biden）的国情咨文。</p><p> “If you get rid of TikTok, Facebook and Zuckerschmuck will double their business. I don&#39;t want Facebook, who cheated in the last Election, doing better.他们是真正的人民公敌！” Trump wrote on <a href="https://truthsocial.com/@realDonaldTrump/posts/112058087970558736">Thursday night</a> .</p></blockquote><p> Pretty soon, MAGA faithful like Vivek Ramaswamy were <a href="https://twitter.com/VivekGRamaswamy/status/1766251076800725229">lining up to agree with Trump</a> .</p><p>观察者很快提出了一个理论，说明特朗普为何翻唱。 Trump recently <a href="https://nymag.com/intelligencer/article/trump-tiktok-ban-reversal-china-jeff-yass-why.html">had a very cordial meeting</a> with the billionaire <a href="https://www.wsj.com/politics/policy/jeff-yass-tiktok-bytedance-ban-congress-15a41ec4">Jeff Yass</a> , who has a $33 billion stake (yes, you read that right) in the Chinese-owned company:</p><blockquote><p> One American who does not [want to force TikTok to sell] is Jeff Yass, a conservative hedge-fund manager who has a $33 billion stake in TikTok and has <a href="https://nypost.com/2024/03/07/us-news/billionaire-tiktok-investor-bullies-lawmakers-to-stop-sale/">reportedly</a> threatened to cut off funding to Republicans who support the divestment bill.</p><p> Last week, Yass visited Mar-a-Lago, where Trump <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/03/01/trump-club-for-growth-00144547">praised</a> him as “fantastic,” and media reports touted that Yass could potentially contribute generously to Trump&#39;s campaign.</p></blockquote><p> Trump <a href="https://apnews.com/article/trump-legal-bills-debt-campaign-fundraising-shortfalls-07c9bafaaa5d4f27d93dbda3bd2624ea">badly needs money</a> ;他的竞选活动正在损害资金，他也遇到了法律麻烦。鉴于这一点，再加上他的腐败记录，他卖给了中国共产党的盟友几美元，这绝对是合理的。这一理论是由前特朗普顾问凯利安·康威（Kellyanne Conway）付给俱乐部的增长以<a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/03/09/kellyanne-conway-tiktok-trump-00146144">促进国会山上的利益</a>的事实来加强了这一理论的；杰夫·亚斯（Jeff Yass）是俱乐部最大的捐助者。</p><p> Tiktok Bill的保守冠军突然发现地毯从他们的脚下拉出。该法案可能仍会通过，但是鉴于众议院共和党人如何在乌克兰援助的 <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2024/02/10/politics/trump-foreign-aid-loan-senate-package/index.html">特朗普后面排队</a>，可以说它的未来现在更加怀疑了。</p><p>如果该法案被击败，那么将希望放在特朗普的中国鹰队来说，这并不只是一生的尴尬。它将允许宣传和间谍软件的引擎继续妥协美国的国家安全。这将表明美国在新兴冷战中的地位危险薄弱。</p><h4> Tiktok真的很糟糕，应该被迫出售</h4><p>首先，让我们谈谈为什么强迫野蛮人出售tiktok很重要。很多人称其为“ Tiktok禁令”，但实际上并非如此。国会中的法案只会迫使蒂克托克的公司所有权改变；视频服务本身以及所有愚蠢的舞蹈视频和坏新闻分析都将保留。</p><p>但值得注意的是，对于蒂克托克（Tiktok）目前的领导而言，所有权的变化也可能与禁令相同： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61eb2ac6-d4e7-42ce-8f87-7402090b1357_908x365.