ws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22c919d8-1f03-4dc6-b240-eefcf7813495_917x217.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22c919d8-1f03-4dc6-b240-eefcf7813495_917x217.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></figure></div><p>其他各种Pro-CCP社交媒体帐户也在<a href="https://twitter.com/thinking_panda/status/1766985203753591081">说同一件事</a>。</p><p>因此，这些人肯定认为Tiktok保持中文和控制至关重要。</p><p>蒂克托克（Tiktok）试图杀死该法案的绝望仅使这一点驱使回家。让我们暂停一下，并考虑到数百万美国<em>儿童</em>的绝对精神错乱，他们在一场临时政治压力运动中签署为步兵：</p><blockquote><p>美国国会办公室已经告诉英国广播公司，他们正在向Tiktok用户的电话辩护，以了解可能被禁止使用的法律。</p><p>一位共和党工作人员透露，呼叫者的范围从青少年到老年人，大多数人“真的很困惑，因为&#39;Tiktok告诉我&#39;&#39;。其中许多是脆弱的学龄儿童”，其中一些是出于安全原因必须标记的极端言论……</p><p> [纽约代表里奇（Ritchie）]托雷斯在给英国广播公司（BBC）的一份声明中说：“我对年轻人称为国会，威胁要自杀或以其他方式伤害自己的报道感到非常困扰。”</p></blockquote><p>实际上，它变得更加荒谬。蒂克托克（Tiktok）<a href="https://fortune.com/2024/03/08/tiktok-non-disparagement-clause-shares-seized/amp/">占领了公开批评它的股东的股票</a>：</p><blockquote><p>批评该公司的现任和前Tiktok员工有可能损失自己拥有的任何股票（在某些情况下价值数百万美元），这是根据股东协议降低社交媒体服务的一项股东协议……五个执业股东法的律师告诉<em>《财富》</em>是不寻常的，但不是非法的……</p><p> Tiktok的股东合同，据<em>《财富》</em>看来，股东不能“直接或间接对公司或公司的任何子公司，分支机构，董事，董事，高级或雇员发表任何关键，不利或贬低的陈述或评论”。如果抓住股东这样做，“参与者的所有限制股单位将立即被没收。”</p></blockquote><p>为什么Tiktok的当前管理和CCP喉舌都如此迫切希望防止出售？毕竟，Tiktok仍然存在，Bytedance将获得数万美元的现金。只有一个答案是有道理的：中国当局认为，蒂克托克是影响美国舆论的重要工具。</p><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-of-course-we-should-ban-tiktok">通常给出迫使Tiktok销售的原因有两个</a>。首先，人们抱怨该应用程序涉足美国人的美国人。这是真实的。该公司一再与美国用户的数据一起做任何许多坏事 - 跟踪批评该公司， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/tiktok-pledged-to-protect-u-s-data-1-5-billion-later-its-still-struggling-cbccf203?mod=followamazon">将私人数据转发</a>给中国母公司的<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2022/dec/22/tiktok-bytedance-workers-fired-data-access-journalists">记者</a>（<a href="https://stratechery.com/2020/the-tiktok-war/">法律规定</a>CCP然后拥有信息），因此在。为防止这些数据滥用而努力的努力是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/tiktok-pledged-to-protect-u-s-data-1-5-billion-later-its-still-struggling-cbccf203">无助</a>，不幸和最终绝望的。</p><p>但是，对Tiktok的更大关注并不是间谍 - 这是<em>宣传</em>。大约三分之一的年轻美国人，总体上有七分之一的美国人，现在经常从该应用中获取新闻： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg" width="600" height="474.2857142857143" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:664,&quot;width&quot;:840,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:600,&quot;bytes&quot;:102483,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fce1c006d-1640-4926-b7c0-8f7d398a42df_840x664.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2023/11/15/more-americans-are-getting-news-on-tiktok-bucking-the-trend-seen-on-most-other-social-media-sites/">长椅</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这里的问题不是年轻人在Tiktok上获得的新闻很<em>糟糕</em>- 大部分<a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/tiktok-osama-bin-laden-antisemitism-6580384e">肯定</a><em><a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/tiktok-osama-bin-laden-antisemitism-6580384e">是</a></em><a href="https://www.wsj.com/tech/tiktok-osama-bin-laden-antisemitism-6580384e">糟糕的</a>，但这与新闻消费者相比，这是一个问题，而不是使用该应用程序。问题在于，该消息是<em>由外国对手政府巧妙而明显地控制的</em>。</p><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-6e5">早在12月，我写了</a>一项最近的研究，表明Tiktok有选择地抑制了CCP关注的主题的视频：</p><blockquote><p> [令人担忧]通过对算法的微妙操纵，Tiktok可以使美国人摆脱对CCP敏感的讨论的主题，并转向CCP批准的观点。</p><p><a href="https://networkcontagion.us/wp-content/uploads/A-Tik-Tok-ing-Timebomb_12.21.23.pdf">网络传染研究所的一项新研究</a>证实，这已经以非常实质性的方式进行。通过比较Instagram和Tiktok上简短视频的主题标签，他们可以了解Tiktok算法令人鼓舞或抑制的主题。</p><p>对于任何熟悉CCP信息抑制的人来说，结果非常不足为奇。涉及一般政治主题（BLM，特朗普，堕胎等）的主题标签在Tiktok上与Instagram一样受欢迎。但是，对CCP敏感的主题（Tiananmen Square大屠杀，香港抗议和镇压等）的主题标签仅在Tiktok上像Instagram上一样普遍。差异绝对令人震惊： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F429fa831-69e8-4faf-bf10-7925282c513c_1042x759.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F429fa831-69e8-4faf-bf10-7925282c513c_1042x759.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F429fa831-69e8-4faf-bf10-7925282c513c_1042x759.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F429fa831-69e8-4faf-bf10-7925282c513c_1042x759.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2