ist of interesting things to write about is getting unmanageably long. So I&#39;m going to have to do a few more and longer roundups, just to keep on top of everything.</p><p> Anyway, first, let&#39;s do podcasts. My friend <a href="https://twitter.com/stephxsher">Stephanie Sher</a> (a tech investor and AI person) and I did a very interesting appearance on our friend <a href="https://twitter.com/noor_siddiqui_">Noor Siddiqui</a> &#39;s podcast, which is called Conceivable. Noor runs a startup called <a href="https://www.orchidhealth.com/">Orchid</a> that does genetic screening for IVF, so she talks about a lot of topics related to fertility and childbearing. Steph wanted to do an episode about dating and romance in the tech world, and I somehow ended up getting roped into this. It&#39;s not a topic I typically talk about, but I like to think I added some interesting perspectives to the mix. We don&#39;t have video, due to a technical error, but the audio is pretty fun: </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a9e32046b143a13439b7bb9cd&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Dating, gendered timelines, and masculine versus feminine energy with Noah Smith and Steph Sher&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noor Siddiqui&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/6UY53r1FMgHBejNOF8cvRT&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/6UY53r1FMgHBejNOF8cvRT" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p> And here it is on <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/conceivable-with-noor/id1721905069?i=1000647549158">Apple Podcasts</a> .</p><p> I also did two episodes of Econ 102, with Erik Torenberg. Here&#39;s one about building a multiracial society. It was inspired by Google&#39;s <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/this-is-not-a-good-way-to-fight-racism">Gemini fiasco</a> , but we end up not even talking about that, and just talking about nationalism and belonging and such. </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a9fcbd27685efd58d05819bad&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Building a Multi Racial Society&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/0ltLXBqGmgBCs7z6PtrNn1&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/0ltLXBqGmgBCs7z6PtrNn1" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p> Here are <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/building-a-multi-racial-society/id1696419056?i=1000647500481">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4pE7ETLp8Mg">YouTube</a> .</p><p> The next episode had a guest, <a href="https://twitter.com/bhargreaves?lang=en">Brad Hargreaves</a> , who writes about real estate. We had a rousing discussion about — you guessed it — the real estate industry and housing.非常有趣。 </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8aca9bd20d0147a068d3808674&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;How We Build More Housing with Brad Hargreaves&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/0KFNapSYYsHb2AQWZyFrlB&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/0KFNapSYYsHb2AQWZyFrlB" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" loading="lazy" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p> And here are <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/how-we-build-more-housing-with-brad-hargreaves/id1696419056?i=1000648060500">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zy16fPt2cVQ">YouTube</a> .</p><p> Anyway, on to this week&#39;s list of at least five interesting things! There are seven items this week, which is technically at least five.</p><h4> 1. Are we better off than in 2019?</h4><p> Every presidential election, the challenger or their supporters ask the famous <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rU6PWT1rVUk">Ronald Reagan question</a> from 1980: “Are you better off than you were four years ago?”. They&#39;re hoping that, like Reagan voters in 1980, people will answer “No,” and vote out the incumbent.</p><p> This week, in advance of Biden&#39;s State of the Union speech, it was Congresswoman Elise Stefanik asking that question: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa957feb3-55e2-46bf-925d-ddffbf749864_915x761.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa957feb3-55e2-46bf-925d-ddffbf749864_915x761.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa957feb3-55e2-46bf-925d-ddffbf749864_915x761.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa957feb3-55e2-46bf-925d-ddffbf749864_915x761.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progress